cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.CR, cs.SI, cs.DS 

This paper deals with the problem of monitoring activities in wireless infrastructure networks, which is a topic related to network infrastructure and communication. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also involves optimization problems and algorithms, which are related to information theory (cs.IT) and cryptography (cs.CR). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of stochastic inference schemes, which is related to statistical learning (cs.SI) and data structures (cs.DS).
